question:
What will be the output of the following code snippet?

try {
    System.out.print("A");
    throw new Exception();
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.print("B");
} finally {
    System.out.print("C");
}

Consider the following code. What is printed to the console?

public static String test() {
    try {
        System.out.print("X");
        return "Y";
    } finally {
        System.out.print("Z");
    }
}

// Method is called: System.out.print(test());
